\par And so on, and so on. On ships, in airports, in expensive hotels, in obscure hotels, in restaurants, on trains. Recognised, questioned, sympathised with, fawned upon}{\insrsid5328970 \emdash }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 
yes, that had been the hardest. Women... Women with eyes like spaniels. Women with that capacity for worship that women had.
\par And then there had been, of course, the Press. For even now he was still news. (Mercifully, }{\i\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 that}{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 
 would not last long.) So many crude brash questions: What are your plans? Would you say now that}{\insrsid5328970 \emdash }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 ? Can I quote you as believing}{\insrsid5328970 \emdash }{
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 ? Can you give us a message?
\par A message, a message, always a message! To the readers of a particular journal, to the country, to men and women, to the world}{\insrsid5328970 \emdash }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 
\par But he had never had a message to give. He had been a messenger, which was a very different thing. But no one was likely to understand that.
\par Rest}{\insrsid5328970 \emdash }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 that was what he had needed. Rest and time. Time to take in what he himself was, and what he should do. Time t
o take stock of himself. Time to start again, at forty, and live his own life. He must find out what had happened to him, to Llewellyn Knox, the man, during the fifteen years he had been employed as a messenger.
\par Sipping his little glass of coloured liqueur
, looking at the people, the lights, the harbour, he thought that this would be a good place to find out all that. It was not the solitude of a desert he wanted, he wanted his fellow kind. He was not by nature a recluse or an ascetic. He had no vocation f
or the monastic life. All he needed was to find out who and what was Llewellyn Knox. Once he knew that, he could go ahead and take up life once more.
\par It all came back, perhaps, to Kant}{\insrsid5328970 \rquote }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 s three questions:
\par }{\i\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 What do I know?
\par What can I hope?
\par What ought I to do?
\par }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5328970 Of these questions, he could answer only one, the second.
